The paper discusses the concept of variable roles in software analysis, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also proposes a classification of variables in a program, which involves analyzing the program's data flow, a topic that is relevant to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the practical applicability of the proposed method in predicting membership of source files to different categories of a software verification competition, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the paper also touches upon the importance of automated software analysis tools in ensuring software correctness, which is a topic that falls under computer security (cs.CR).
